        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>disable_caches</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Disable instruction and data caches for the platform. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function disables the instruction and data caches for MicroBlaze architecture if they are configured in the hardware design. This is typically called during platform cleanup.</para><para><simplesect kind="return"><para>None</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This function only affects MicroBlaze processors. PowerPC cache disabling is not implemented in this function. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
