        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void init_uart</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>init_uart</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Initialize the UART for the platform. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function initializes the UART based on the platform configuration. For 16550 UART (when STDOUT_IS_16550 is defined), it configures the baud rate and line control register for 8 data bits. For PS7/PSU UART, the bootrom/BSP configures it to 115200 bps by default.</para><para><simplesect kind="return"><para>None</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>For 16550 UART, the baud rate is set to UART_BAUD (9600). </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
